The Economic Freedom Fighters will celebrate its 6th birthday on Saturday in Mpumalanga. JOHANNESBURG - The Economic Freedom Fighters will celebrate its 6th birthday on Saturday in Mpumalanga. The party will hold celebrations for its 6th anniversary at the KaNyamazane stadium. Party leader Julius Malema will address the celebrations. In the May election, the EFF received over 10 percent of the vote, almost doubling the 6 percent they received in 2014 national election. It also became the official opposition in three provinces.